<HEADLINE> Contact Group Meeting not to Take Place in London, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 7 (Xinhua) -- British Foreign Office said on
Wednesday that a proposed Thursday meeting of the six-nation
Contact Group to discuss the Kosovo crisis would not take place.
</P>
<P>
"The meeting will not be taking place," a Foreign Office
spokesman said, but he gave no further details.
</P>
<P>
Reuters earlier quoted a Western diplomat as saying that
foreign ministers of the six-nation Contact Group on former
Yugoslavia were likely to meet in London on Thursday to discuss
the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
The change of plan suggested splits among the six members of
the group over whether to use military force against Yugoslav
targets in retaliation for Belgrade's bloody crackdown in Kosovo.
Russia has been strongly opposed to using air strikes to solve the
Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Contact Group comprises Britain, the United States, France,
Germany, Italy as well as Russia.
</P>
<P>
France and Russia announced earlier on Wednesday that they were
sending their foreign ministers to take part in the meeting.
</P>
</TEXT>
