<HEADLINE> URGENT: Pakistan's Army Chief Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Army Chief and
Chairman of the Joint Chiefs Staff Committee General Jahangir
Karamat resigned from his office Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to Pakistan Television (PTV), Karamat sent a letter
to Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif requesting him to accept the
resignation.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister has accepted Karamat's resignation and has
appointed Lt. General Pervez Musharaf as the new army chief.
</P>
<P>
Karamat said in his letter that he had proposed the
establishment of the National Security Council. However,
unnecessary debate has started on the issue, so he decided to step
down "to establish a good tradition for the future."  
</P>
</TEXT>
