<HEADLINE> EU Presses for Immediate Elections in Congo (K) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) special
envoy to the Great Lakes region Aldo Ajello Wednesday pressed for
an "immediate" general election in the Democratic Republic of
Congo (DRC).
</P>
<P>
The solution to the conflicts in the Great Lakes region,
especially in the DRC should be through political means, and the
"so-called military settlement won't do," Ajello told the press
here before his departure.
</P>
<P>
The EU hopes that an immediate and fair general election will
be held in the DRC, he added.
</P>
<P>
The envoy admitted that to hold elections now may encounter
many difficulties such as amending the constitution, making
election law and voter registration. But he was quick to add
that the EU is willing to "provide financial aid for the election
in the DRC."
</P>
<P>
During his two-day visit in Angola, Ajello held talks with
President Eduardo dos Santos and Prime Minister Franca Van-dunem.
</P>
<P>
He described the talks as "positive", adding they reached
consensus on "political solution to regional crisis."
</P>
<P>
The EU envoy will also visit Rwanda to continue his African
tour which has already covered Ethiopia, Uganda, Zimbabwe, South
Africa, Mozambique and Zambia where he held consultations with
the leaders on the tension in the DRC. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
