<HEADLINE> 10 Arrested in Sierra Leone for Lottery Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Sierra Leonean police said
Wednesday that they have arrested 10 persons, including former
top officials at the national lottery, in connection with a fire
that destroyed the lottery headquarters.
</P>
<P>
A report from capital Freetown quoted officers at the criminal
investigations department as saying that those arrested include
the former deputy manager, company secretary and chief
accountant, all sacked two weeks ago after fraud was uncovered in
the lottery.
</P>
<P>
Security guards said Sunday's fire started on the top floor of
the three-story building in central Freetown and that the
lottery's accounting records were presumed to have been
destroyed.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the suspected arson has caused
outrage in Freetown, with radio stations bombarded by callers
demanding that the lottery officials be charged.
</P>
<P>
The government has told police investigators to wrap up their
inquiry quickly so that charges can be pressed, added the report.
</P>
</TEXT>
