<HEADLINE> Ethiopia, South Africa to Set Up Joint Brewery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 7 (Xinhua) -- A group of Ethiopian and
South African investors will set up a joint brewery in Akaki,
some 20 kilometers south of the Ethiopian capital Addis Ababa.
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here Wednesday said the investors signed an
agreement with local officials Tuesday which enabled them to
acquire 21 hectares of land on lease.
</P>
<P>
The joint brewery will be built at a cost of over 300 million
Birr (42 million U.S. Dollars), 51 percent of which will be
covered by Ethiopians and the remaining by the South African
side.
</P>
<P>
The brewery will start operation in one year's time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
