<HEADLINE> Gunmen Rob 22 Million Shillings from Bank in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Unidentified gunmen broke into
the Victoria Commercial Bank in downtown Nairobi Wednesday,
running away with 22 million Shillings (370,000 U.S. Dollars).
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said there were brief exchange of gun fires but
nobody was hurt. The robbery happened at 7:30 a.m. local time.
</P>
<P>
The neighboring South African embassy was the victim of a
false alarm caused by the robbery as three bullets hit through
its windows facing the street.
</P>
<P>
The police later confirmed the incident, claiming that five of
the nine bandits have been arrested.
</P>
<P>
However, the looted money has not been recovered yet,
according to the Kenya Television Network (KTN) broadcasting.
</P>
<P>
Also on Wednesday, the police gunned down three armed robbers
and seized three revolvers and 68 rounds of bullets in the
northeast of the Kenyan capital.
</P>
<P>
Nairobi has seen an upsurge of robberies and other violent
crimes over the past months.
</P>
<P>
The bank attack also came amid a one-month banking crisis in
which four commercial banks had fallen and there are strong
rumors that another three will follow suit by run of depositors.
</P>
<P>
Kenya has 55 commercial banks and financial institutions,
about 12 of which are branches of foreign banks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
