<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Film Corporation to Be Dissolved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Film
Corporation will be dissolved due to its failure to meet its
objectives, the Ethiopian News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A statement attached to the bill liquidating the corporation
said the corporation could not generate its own income for it has
handed over cinema halls previously under its administration to
various regions.
</P>
<P>
The corporation, which was established in 1986, is also unable
to produce films, and it could no longer continue as a public
enterprise due to its failure to live up to expectations, said
the statement.
</P>
<P>
According to the statement, the debt the corporation owes the
government and other parties has amounted to 4.01 million Birr
(about 564,000 U.S. Dollars) and the debt will be paid back from
the sale of the corporation's assets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
