<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambican Youths Urged to Play Bigger Role in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, October 7 (Xinhua) -- President Joaquim Chissano
called on the youths in the country here Wednesday to play a more
active role in the drive to build a prosperous Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the forth national conference of the Organization
of Mozambican Youths, Chissano said the government recognizes the
potential of the youths and gives priority to their education,
housing employment and other issues in the five-year plan.
</P>
<P>
The youths should be pioneers to meet the challenge of the new
century, and should show special attention to the development of
information and communication, he noted.
</P>
<P>
But it is pity that many of the youths become "illiterate" in
terms of computer, and many have even never touched a
type-writer, not to speak of a computer, Chissano said.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting attended by about 250 delegates, Chissano said
plan should be mapped out to attract youths in future social
construction programs.
</P>
<P>
Mozambique won its independence in 1975, but 16 years of civil
war has brought great losses to the conntry's economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
