with U.S. President Bill Clinton next Thursday in Washinton for an
agreement on the long-delayed Israeli withdrawal from the West
Bank.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians and Israel are striving to narrow their gaps
over a U.S. proposal demanding Israel to pull back from a further
13 percent of the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
Moussa said that he is scheduled to meet with U.S. Assistant
Secretary of State Martin Indyk Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Indyk will arrive here later Wednesday to inform Egypt about
the results of the Palestinian-Israeli talks held in the past two
days and the U.S. efforts to salvage the long-stalled peace
process. 
