<HEADLINE> Khamenei Criticizes Conspirators Misusing Freedom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Iran's paramount leader
Ayatollah Ali Khamenei Wednesday criticized once again "certain
conspirators misusing freedom of expression."
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with officials of the Construction Jihad
Ministry, Khamenei noted that expressing different views is
different from treason and conspiracy, the official news agency
IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
It was the second time in one month that Khamenei has called
for stopping misuse of freedom of expression in the country.
</P>
<P>
A group of dailies and weeklies, mainly from the leftist and
moderate factions, were closed down by the conservative judiciary
after the Iranian leader urged the relevant authorities last
month to seriously deal with freedom-abusing by the press.
</P>
<P>
Certain elements have embarked on sabotaging the government's
economic programs, launching an offensive against the security,
cultural and military structures in an attempt to undermine the
main pillars of the Islamic Republic of Iran, Khamenei said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the conspirators are trying to weaken the youth's
hope for their future and misuse every means to strike a blow at
the Islamic Republic of Iran.
</P>
<P>
"We have said time and again that expressing views on every
issue is free and those having objections to the government's
plans are entitled to publish their objections and no one will
stop them," he said, "but there exists a fundamental difference
between objection and sabotage."
</P>
<P>
He said "critique and criticism of the government's policies
are not bad, but when someone attempts to undermine the
foundations of the government, it is a treason and not freedom of
expression ... The enemy's hands are seen in such practices."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
