<HEADLINE> Kenya Opens 3rd Int'l Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap
Moi Wednesday officially opened the western Eldoret International
Airport, the third in this east African country.
</P>
<P>
"This is an important milestone in my government's efforts to
develop an effective air transportation," a report quoted Moi as
saying at a ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The airport is strategically located in the western part of
Kenya in order to facilitate increased exploitation of the large
potential for agricultural and industrial growth in east African
region, he said. Eldoret is the fifth biggest city of the
country.
</P>
<P>
The airport is widely expected to promote the western and
northwestern tourist circuits and promote trade links among the
East African Cooperation and the Common Market for Eastern and
Southern Africa.
</P>
<P>
So far over 6,000 tons of flowers have been exported through
this airport directly to international markets.
</P>
<P>
Moi said the airport will take favorable measures including
scheduled services, grant unrestricted access to non-scheduled
flights, lower landing fee, free parking of aircraft and reduced
charges for air navigation services so as to attract customers.
</P>
<P>
Moi also said there is an urgent need to formulate policies to
further strengthen Kenya's central location in east African
region and enhance its growth and development into a commercial
and air transport hub for the region and beyond. 
</P>
</TEXT>
