<HEADLINE> Khatami Announces Readiness to Mediate between </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad
Khatami Wednesday announced his readiness to mediate between
Turkey and Syria to defuse the spiraling tensions between them.
</P>
<P>
Khatami made the announcement in his separate telephone
conversations with his Syrian counterpart Hafez al-Assad and
Turkish counterpart Suleyman Demirel, the official news agency
IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
He said that he was ready to go personally or to send Foreign
Minister Kamal Kharrazi to Turkey and Syria to help the two
neighbors settle their differences.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian president also announced readiness to host al-Assad
and Demirel in Tehran to reach a reconciliation between Damascus
and Ankara.
</P>
<P>
With a war of words escalating recently, relations between
Turkey and Syria have deteriorated.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has accused Syria of harboring and supporting the
Kurdish Workers' Party rebels fighting for autonomy in southeast
Turkey. Syria has denied the charge.
</P>
<P>
Expressing concern over the ongoing tensions between Turkey and
Syria, Khatami underlined the need for the two Muslim neighbors
to solve their problems through political negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The tensions between two Muslim neighbors will not benefit any
country in the region but the enemies of Muslims and those who do
not want tranquility in the region, he said.
</P>
<P>
Khatami called on Turkey and Syria to stop any action and
propaganda against each other, adding that resorting to force and
threat would only intensify the problems between Muslim brothers.
</P>
<P>
Both al-Assad and Demirel expressed welcome to any initiatives
by Iran to defuse the tensions, IRNA said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
