<HEADLINE> Jordan Still Undecides His Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Michael Jordan has one foot
out of the NBA door, but the league's marquee player told the
press Wednesday he is not ruling out returning to the Chicago
Bulls.
</P>
<P>
"What's most important right now is for me to see where the
league is going, then look deep inside myslef to make a clear-cut
decision. So for now, I'm keeping my options open," Jordan was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Jordan, 35, said his final decision must await the conclusion
of the NBA lockout. He also said he isn't opposed to playing for
Tim Floyd or for an organization still run by general manager
Jerry Krause.
</P>
<P>
"I played with Jerry the last five or six season, and we've
been successful," Jordan said. "I don't like it. But that's not
going to be my final deciding factor." 
</P>
