<HEADLINE> 20 French Pensioners Killed as Boat Sinks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, October 8 (Xinhua) -- At least 20 French pensioners
died and 44 were injured when their excursion boat sank in a lake
in northeastern Spain Thursday morning.
</P>
<P>
Another 78 passenger aboard the boat Anna escaped unhurt.
</P>
<P>
The boat, whose passengers are believed to be French pensioners
from La Rochelle area of western France, sank as it began a
sightseeing tour of Lake Banyoles, the largest lake in Catalonia.
</P>
<P>
The national news agency Efe quoted witnesses as saying the
boat split in two about a dozen meters from the bank and
panic-stricken passengers jumped into the water.
</P>
<P>
"The problem is that the passengers were old folk and that made
it difficult for them to swim ashore," a spokesman for La Carpa,
the company that owns Anna, said.
</P>
<P>
A large number of ambulances and helicopters rushed to the
scene of the accident.
</P>
<P>
Rescue crews worked for hours, searching for survivors and
transporting the injured to the Salus hospital in Banyoles and a
hospital in nearby Gerone.
</P>
<P>
Sources also said French officials were heading for the site,
arranging to sent the dead and the injured back to France.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident still unknown. 
</P>
</TEXT>
