<HEADLINE> Italian Drug-testing Lab Closes Temporarily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 8 (Xinhua) -- The Italian Olympic Committee's
medical federation said its drug-testing laboratory will be shut
down for allegedly cover-up of doping tests in soccer.
</P>
<P>
Acqua Acetosa will close Friday and tests that would have been
conducted at the lab will be sent to labs in Barcelona, Spain,
Cologne, Germany, or Lausanne, Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
The International Olympic Committee (IOC) made the decision
after investigators from the Rome prosecutor's office searched
the homes of five current or former employees of the lab, who
were alleged to conceal evidence and abuse the office.
</P>
<P>
Reports said the doping tests of Italian League soccer had not
been fully carried out and the results may have been hidden.
Documentation of anti-doping tests, which was required to keep at
least two years, was being discarded after two months, with five
in the case of positive tests. 
</P>
</TEXT>
