<HEADLINE> Chinese President Praises Military's Political Consciousness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin,
at a meeting today celebrating the victory over the flood fighting
this summer, praised the Chinese armed forces for their more than
two months of work in fighting floods and rescuing people.
</P>
<P>
The people's armed forces demonstrated a high degree of
political consciousness in carrying out Party instructions and
putting the people's interests first, said Jiang Zemin, who is
also general secretary of the Chinese Communist Party Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
The PLA and Armed Police acted as "shock troops" in the fight
against the flood and made a tremendous contribution by being the
mainstay in the operations, added Jiang who is also chairman of
the Central Military Commission (CMC).
</P>
<P>
They sent some 300,000 soldiers to reinforce dykes and rescue
people stranded by the worst flooding on the Yangtze River and the
Nenjiang and Songhua rivers in northeast China. They also flew
2,200 sorties and used 12,500 vehicles and 1,170 ships, Jiang
added.
</P>
<P>
"Our military has lived up to the expectations of the Party and
the people and fulfilled the tasks in a perfect way," Jiang said,
adding that it proved that it is capable of prompt action and
resolute command and keeps the fine tradition of facing hardships
and fearing nothing.
</P>
</TEXT>
