<HEADLINE> Tajik Opposition Politician Appointed Deputy PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Tajik President Emomali
Rakhmonov has signed a decree appointing Zokir Vazirov, a key
member of the United Tajik Opposition (UTO), deputy prime minister
of the country, the Interfax news agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Vazirov, 50 and former minister of education, will be in charge
of social issues and regional autonomy.
</P>
<P>
The Tajik president's spokesman was quoted as saying that the
appointment came after Rakhmonov's Wednesday meeting with Abdullo
Nuri, the leader of the UTO and head of the National
Reconciliation Commission.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that the appointment was made in accordance
with the general treaty of peace and national accord signed in
June, 1997, under which the opposition will have 30 percent of the
seats in the government and local executive bodies.
</P>
<P>
Since February, Rakhmonov has appointed 12 UTO members as
government ministers. On March 10, Khodj-Akbar Turajonzod, one of
the major UTO leaders, was appointed as the first deputy prime
minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
