<HEADLINE> Date for Kazakh Presidential Election Brought Forward </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan decided on Thursday
to bring forward its presidential election to January 10, only
three months away.
</P>
<P>
The decision was approved by the the parliament with a vote of
100-0 and with one abstention.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, President Nursultan Nazarbayev accepted the
newly-set polling date and agreed to cut short his term as
president, the end of which was previously scheduled for the year
2000.
</P>
<P>
Nazarbayev, the first president since the nation's independence
in 1991, succeeded in extending his term of office through a
national referendum held in April, 1995
</P>
<P>
Reports said deputies called for early elections for the sake
of economic and political reasons.
</P>
<P>
They are also seeking a series of changes to electoral law.
</P>
