<HEADLINE> Mongolian President Presents Six Candidates for PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Mongolian President Nachagyn
Bagabandy on Thursday presented six candidates for prime minister
to the ruling coalition, the Mongolian National Democratic Party
(MNDP) and Social Democratic Party (SDP).
</P>
<P>
Bagabandy said that in view of the coalition's repeated failure
to nominate a qualified candidate, the nomination of any one of
the six could be directly submitted to the Great Hural
(parliament) for approval.
</P>
<P>
The six candidates are Dogsm Ganbold, Tsevelma Bayarsaikhan,
Janlav Naranchachralt, Luvsanbaldan Nyamsambuu and Jugnee
Amarsanaa from the MNDP and Sharavjamts Batbayar from the SDP.
</P>
<P>
Under Mongolian law, the ruling party must discuss its
nomination for prime minister with the president, who in turn
submits it to the Great Hural for approval.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the president rejected several nominations made by the
coalition.
</P>
<P>
Bagabandy said that in a bid to end the two-month government
crisis earlier, he presented the six candidates by himself this
time.
</P>
<P>
A decision in May to merge the state-owned Renovation Bank with
the private Golomt Bank resulted in the dismissal of Prime
Minister Tsakhya Elbegdorj's government in July. Under the
Mongolian, a new prime minister should be appointed within 30 days
of the dismissal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
