<HEADLINE> Palestinians, Israeli Soldiers Clash in Hebron </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Several people were injured in
clashes between Palestinian protesters and Israeli soldiers
Thursday in the West Bank city of Hebron, a Palestinian press
service reported.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of Palestinians threw stones at Israeli soldiers
guarding Jewish enclaves in the Israeli-controlled downtown sector
and the soldiers responded with rubber bullets, the Jerusalem
Media and Communication Center (JMCC) said.
</P>
<P>
Several Palestinians were injured, including a AFP cameraman
Hussam Abu Alan who was seriously wounded by a bullet hit in the
head and underwent emergency surgery in a Hebron hospital.
</P>
<P>
Palestinians in Hebron launched a general strike Thursday to
protest against an eight-day blockade and a curfew in downtown
area.
</P>
<P>
Israel lifted the closure Thursday morning, but the curfew
remained in effect, confining some 30,000 Palestinians to their
homes.
</P>
<P>
The closure and curfew were imposed by Israeli army last
Wednesday after some 20 Israeli soldiers and Palestinian
civilians were wounded in a hand grenade attack in the downtown
Hebron.
</P>
<P>
The general strike echoed calls by the Palestinian National
Liberation Movement (Fatah) Tuesday, which appealed for strike and
demonstrations in Hebron unless the blockade and curfew were both
lifted.
</P>
<P>
Hebron, a flash point of clashes between Palestinians and
Israelis, is home to 130,000 Palestinians and 450 Jewish settlers
who live in different enclaves in the city with heavy protection
of Israeli soliders. 
</P>
</TEXT>
