<HEADLINE> British Prime Minister in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister Tony Blair
attended the opening ceremony of Britain's first insurance company
in China, in Shanghai, today.
</P>
<P>
The presence of the Royal &AMP; SunAlliance Insurance Company in
Shanghai shows Britain's confidence in the economic prospects of
the metropolitan and China as well, Blair said.
</P>
<P>
Royal &AMP; Sun, whose headquarters are in London, has three
centuries of experience in the international insurance business
and is one of the world's top ten insurance companies.
</P>
<P>
Its contacts with China go back a century. As early as 1853, it
set up business in Shanghai, then set up its first representative
office in Beijing, and another two in Dalian and Shanghai.
</P>
