<HEADLINE> Autopsy Shows Canadian Pro Dies from Heart Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 8 (Xinhua) -- An Autopsy for Stephane Miron, who
collapsed and died in a German ice hockey league match on
Tuesday, showed that the Canadian professional had already
suffered one heart attack years before.
</P>
<P>
Miron, 29, died minutes after he scored a goal for Berlin
Capitals in Oberhausen. He collapsed on the bench during the
second period and never woke up again.
</P>
<P>
The autopsy found Miron had suffered a heart attack several
years ago and also chronic bronchitis, which had gone unrecognis
ed, police said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Capitals denied any rumors linked the death with doping,
saying the Canadian had passed a routine health check two months
ago.  
