<HEADLINE> U.N. Chief to Visit Seoul for Peace Prize </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, October 8 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan
will visit South Korea on October 22-24 to receive the Seoul Peace
Prize, the Foreign Affairs and Trade Ministry said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Annan was chosen from some 60 nominations submitted form around
the world by the Seoul Peace Prize Committee last month. The
awarding ceremony will fall on October 23.
</P>
<P>
"After several rounds of screening, the committee decided to
bestow this year's award on Annan in recognition of his
distinguished contributions to world peace through international
diplomatic and humanitarian endeavors," said Lee Chul-seung,
chairman of the 15-member Seoul Peace Prize Committee.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in South Korea, Annan is expected to meet with
President Kim Dae-jung and other South Korean leaders.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first time for Annan to visit Seoul after he
took top U.N. post in January 1997.
</P>
<P>
The Seoul Peace Prize Committee, established in 1990 to
commemorate Seoul's successful hosting of the 1988 Olympic Games,
issues an award every two years, with its winner receiving a cash
prize of 200,000 U.S. dollars. 
</P>
