<HEADLINE> Military Clashes Occur Between Iran and Taliban </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Iranian troops clashed with the
Afghan Taliban militia Thursday morning on Iran's northeastern
border area, Iranian television reported.
</P>
<P>
Taliban militants raided Iranian border posts in northeastern
Khorasan province early Thursday and Iranian border guards
returned fire, repulsing the attackers.
</P>
<P>
According to the official news agency IRNA, commander of the
ground forces of the Islamic Revolutionary Guards Corps (IRGC)
Azizollah Jafari said the exchange of fire, which occurred at 6:30
a.m. (0300 GMT) in Salehabad, lasted three hours.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Taliban militants used mortars and
machine-guns in what he called a Taliban aggression, and suffered
heavy casualties after Iranian forces launched a counter attack.
</P>
<P>
Three border posts of the Taliban were totally destroyed by the
15th division of the IRGC in the counter attack, he said, without
giving details.
</P>
<P>
He said the situation in the region has now returned calm.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the Iranian armed forces were on alert to
"deal with any Taliban border provocation" in eastern Iran.
</P>
<P>
There was no report of casualties on the Iranian side.
</P>
<P>
Tensions have been mounting between Iran and the Taliban, after
dozens of Iranian nationals were killed or captured by the student
militia in northern Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Tehran has vowed to avenge the Taliban killings and massed some
270,000 troops along the border in an attempt to put more pressure
to bear on the Taliban.



