<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Current Account Surplus Rises in 2nd Quarter 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's current account
surplus increased by 28.8 percent in the second quarter of 1998,
according to the Statistics Department Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The surplus in the April-June quarter 1998 reached 8.5 billion
ringgit (2.236 billion U.S. dollars) from a surplus of 6.6 billion
ringgit (about 1.736 billion U.S. dollars) in the first quarter
this year, a statement from the Statistics Department said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the current account surplus during the first half of
1998 was 15.1 billion ringgit (about 3.973 billion U.S. dollars),
compared with a deficit of 10.1 billion ringgit (about 2.657
billion U.S. dollars) during the corresponding period 1997.
</P>
<P>
The department said merchandise exports remained strong in the
second quarter of 1998. However, after four successive quarters of
increase, merchandise exports edged down marginally by 2.9 percent
to 67.1 billion ringgit (about 17.657 billion U.S. dollars)
against 69.1 billion ringgit (about 18.184 billion U.S. dollars)
in the previous quarter, it added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, merchandise imports continued to contract by 8.5
percent for the second straight quarter to reach 52.7 billion
ringgit (about 13.868 billion U.S. dollars) from 57.6 billion
ringgit (about 15.157 billion U.S. dollars) in the first quarter.
</P>
<P>
Given the slower rate of decline in merchandise exports against
merchandise imports, the merchandise surplus was driven to a new
high of 14.4 billion ringgit (about 3.789 billion U.S. dollars),
it said.
</P>
<P>
Due to investment income and other services, the department
said the improvement in the services account deficit during the
first quarter of 1998 was not sustained with the deficit worsening
by 14.6 percent to 4.7 billion ringgit (about 1.236 billion U.S.
dollars) in the April-June 1998 quarter as opposed to a deficit of
4.1 billion ringgit (about 1.078 billion U.S. dollars) in the
first quarter this year.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of 1998, the net services account deficit
amounted to 8.8 billion ringgit (about 2.315 billion U.S. dollars)
compared to 10.3 billion ringgit (about 2.71 billion U.S. dollars)
in the same period 1997, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
