<HEADLINE> More Acid Rains for India: Scientists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 8 (Xinhua) -- India is expected to receive
more and more showers of acidic rain in future if the present
trend of industrial and traffic emissions continue, scientists
warned.
</P>
<P>
In the latest issue of the journal Current Science, Indian
scientists said that the major contributors to acid rain are
oxides of sulfur and nitrogen, while organic acids and to some
extent hydrochloric acid also make rain acidic.
</P>
<P>
Sources of the acid rain are industrial emissions, coal-based
thermal power plants and petrol and diesel burning vehicles.
</P>
<P>
Acid rain may destabilize the entire ecosystem by completely
wiping out several forests and aquatic species and distorting the
food chain, they said.
</P>
<P>
Scientists have found an increasing trend towards acidification
almost all over the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981008.0137 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Expected to Be World's Largest Tourist Destination by 2020 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 8 (Xinhua) -- China is expected to be the
world's largest tourist destination and the fourth largest
tour-abroad market by 2020, the World Tourism Organization (WTO)
has predicted.
</P>
<P>
An increasing number of tourists will choose China as their
destination, with the development of the country's rich tourism
resources and the upgrading of tourist facilities, according to a
WTO annual report issued recently.
</P>
<P>
And by 2020, about 100 million Chinese will tour abroad, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
China will make efforts to protect historical relics and the
natural environment, combine the development of land, sea, and air
transport, and accelerate the construction of tourist resorts,
said He Guangwei, chairman of the China National Tourism
Administration, adding that a dozen State-level holiday resorts
are now being built.
</P>
<P>
China expects some Asian countries to recover from the
financial crisis soon, at which time more of their people will
once again be touring abroad. Chinese tourism departments are
promoting sales in the United States and Europe, and China also
wants to develop tourism with neighboring countries including Viet
Nam and India, the official said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the number of Russian tourists is expected to grow
50 percent this year on the basis of 813,700 visitors in 1997.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Chinese government will develop tourism abroad
for the Chinese with planning and within limits.
</P>
<P>
At present, Chinese tourists can only go to seven countries
including Singapore, Thailand, and the Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that China played host to 57.59 million
overseas tourists last year, ranking 8th in the world,
and bringing in earnings of 12.07 billion U.S. dollars. Overseas
tourism income is expected to hit 38 billion U.S. dollars in 2010.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
