<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed mixed Thursday in quiet trading.
</P>
<P>
Investors focused on speculative as well as selective
bluechips, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stock Composite Index was up 2.09
points to 372.99, the all-share Emas Index added 0.35 of a point
to 98.63, the Industrial Index gained 9.69 points to 742.94 while
the Second Board Index shed 0.17 of a point to 91.35.
</P>
<P>
Advancers led decliners by 257 to 242 while 159 counters were
unchanged, 258 untraded and 33 suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover fell to 75.792 million shares valued at
102.765 million ringgit (about 27.043 million U.S. dollars) from
Wednesday's 168.758 million shares worth 244.842 million ringgit
(about 64.432 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the Main Board decreased to 71.517 million shares
valued at 96.404 million ringgit (about 25.369 million U.S.
dollars) from 162.413 million shares worth 234.989 million ringgit
(about 61.839 million U.S. dollars) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Second Board turnover declined to 4.275 million shares
worth 6.361 million ringgit (about 1.673 million U.S. dollars)
from 6.345 million shares valued at 9.852 million ringgit (about
2.592 million U.S. dollars) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
However, off-market turnover increased to 3.020 million shares
worth 11.106 million ringgit (about 2.922 million U.S. dollars)
from Wednesday's 2.012 million shares totaling 3.460 million
ringgit (about 0.91 million U.S. dollars). 
</P>
