<HEADLINE> Malaysia Donates Winter Clothing, Medicine to Kosovo Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia has donated winter
clothing and medicine to Kosovo refugees, according to a senior
official of the Salam Foundation of Malaysia Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Foundation Chief Executive Mohd Anuar Tahir said in a
statement that the ship carrying 224 boxes of winter clothing and
medicine left Port Klang near here on September 29 and was
scheduled to arrive at Port Durres, Albania, at the end of this
month.
</P>
<P>
He said that from Port Durres the items would be taken to
Kosovo where it would be distributed to the refugees by Khairil
Annuar, director of the Malaysian Relief Center-Islamic Youth
Movement of Malaysia in Sarajevo.
</P>
<P>
He said a sum of 25,000 ringgit (about 6,578 U.S. dollars) was
collected from Malaysians via the winter aid campaign for the
Kosovo people, which was launched by the foundation on July 21.
</P>
<P>
Mohd Anuar also said he would seek help from Malaysia Airlines
to ferry more winter clothing, which was being donated by the
people, to the Kosovo refugees who have been fleeing the war-torn
province. 
</P>
