<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close 2.52 Percent Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks gained 194.79
points, or 2.52 percent, to close at 7,939.51 on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The sharp growth of the share prices was mainly attributed to
the active buying on property stocks as a response to Chief
Executive Tung Chee Hwa's announcement of stabilizing property
prices in his second Policy Address on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The property shares leapt 710.04 points, or 8.32 percent, to
9,248.86 on Thursday. The market was also boosted by the stronger
Japanese yen and lower local interbank rates.
</P>
<P>
Thursday's turnover amounted to 5.835 billion HK dollars (748
million U.S. dollars), 2.026 billion HK dollars (260 million U.S.
dollars) more than that in the previous trading day.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index fell 30.64 points, or 0.40 percent, to open
at 7,714.08 Thursday morning.
</P>
<P>
It was then 292.43 points, or 3.78 percent, up when the market
closed at lunch break.
</P>
<P>
The share prices rose 180.18 points, or 2.38 percent, to close
at 7,744.72 on Wednesday.  
</P>
