<HEADLINE> 2nd APEC Technology Exchange Conference, Exhibition Fair Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANTAI, October 8 (Xinhua) -- The second Asia-Pacific Economic
Cooperation (APEC) small and medium-sized enterprise technology
exchange conference and exhibition fair opened today in this port
city in east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
Featuring "friendship, cooperation, development and
prosperity," the fair is meant to increase technological exchanges
and cooperation and promote trade and investment among medium and
small APEC-member enterprises, and advance economic development
and prosperity in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The APEC includes 21 member nations comprising 42.5 percent of
the world's population, with their GDP and international trade
accounting for over 50 percent and 48 percent of the world's
total, respectively.
</P>
<P>
While announcing the opening of the fair, Chinese Vice-Premier
Wu Bangguo called for intensified exchanges and cooperation in
economic and technological fields to advance the economic growth
of APEC member states.
</P>
<P>
The fair, with more than 1,000 business booths, has received a
total of 198 academic papers, 100 of which will be read during the
exhibition.
</P>
<P>
During the conference, which is under the auspices of the APEC
and the Chinese State Commission of Economy and Trade, discussions
of academic papers, displays of commodities, and economic and
trade negotiations will be conducted.
</P>
<P>
The fair will last until October 14.  
</P>
</TEXT>
