<HEADLINE> S.Korea's Auto Export Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, October 8 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's car export hit 116,950
units in September this year, a 71-percent surge from August due to
rising overseas demand, the Korea Automobile Manufacturers
Association said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It also showed a 33.6 percent rise over the export figure
registered in the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
The rise has narrowed the year-on-year rate of car export from
minus 12.4 percent in the first eight months of 1998 to minus 2.6
percent in the first nine months of this year.
</P>
<P>
South Korea's auto export suffered serious setbacks in May-August
this year with the export down on a monthly average of 23 percent.
</P>
<P>
So far this year, Daewoo Motor Co. has exported 264,400 units to
nine countries, exceeding its export target of 219,700 units.
</P>
<P>
Hyundai Motor Co. shipped out 54,916 units in September alone, up
30.6 percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The association attributed increasing car export to the success of
South Korean automakers' overseas sales promotion activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
