unimportant issues such as asking for recounting the ballots,
changing the seat calculation formula and granting amnesty to five
opposition figures.
</P>
<P>
"It was widely believed that the working groups of three
parties have made no significant progress on the formation of the
government and other important issues, although they have been
working hard," he said.
</P>
<P>
"So, I hope the three major political parties speed up the
process and working even harder for the sake of the interests of
the nation and the country. To Cambodia, time is money," he
stressed.
</P>
<P>
