National Assembly function and a new government formed at the
second or third week of October.
</P>
<P>
"Hun Sen and I are prepared to hold talks with the Funcinpec
party President Prince Ranariddh at any time. We hope the Prince
come back from Bangkok as soon as possible," Chea Sim stated.
</P>
<P>
Ranariddh and opposition party leader Sam Rainsy left Siem Reap
for Bangkok on September 25, the day after the opening of the
National Assembly and the lifting of a travel ban on opposition
members, allegedly for personal, not political reasons. Sam Rainsy
is now in the United States to lobby the U.S. government not to
accept the Cambodian government formed by Second Prime Minister
Hun Sen.
</P>
<P>
Now only 25 of the 43 Funcinpec Parliamentarians are in
Cambodia and the 15 of Sam Rainsy Party's Assembly members are all
out of the country.
</P>
<P>
Chem Sim called on all the parliamentarians to do their duty
and come back soon. He pledged there was no threats against their
parliamentary immunity and the King's stay in Phnom Penh has
provided the safeguard.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Chea Sim said the better way is through the three
party working group session and the two party meeting between the
CPP and Funcinpec being held simultaneously, because some
important issues were only directly related to the CPP and
Funcinpec.
</P>
<P>
When asked about Sam Rainsy, Chem Sim said Sam Rainsy has only
two choices, one is to participate in the coalition government and
other is to continue to act as an opposition party. 
</P>
