<HEADLINE> India's Train Accident Kills Seven People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Seven passengers were killed
and 11 others seriously injured when 10 bogies of an express train
derailed in Guntur district of Andhra Pradesh in southern India
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that a medical relief train had been
rushed to the accident site and the injured had been admitted to
the government general hospital for treatment. The railway control
room said incessant rains in the area were hampering rescue
operations.
</P>
<P>
A number of trains have been diverted or canceled due to
disruption of traffic in the sector.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the train accident is yet to be known. Senior
railway and district officials have rushed to the accident site to
supervise rescue and relief operations. 
</P>
