<HEADLINE> China Science News Set to Become Daily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 8 (Xinhua) -- The China Science News, one of
China's major science newspapers established in 1959, will become
the Science Daily on January 1, 1999.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS) will establish the daily
along with the academies of Engineering (CAE) and Social Sciences
(CASS), according Editor in Chief Luo Rongxing.
</P>
<P>
"The new newspaper will become part of the mainstream science
media serving 20 million intellectuals across the country," said
Luo.
</P>
<P>
The existing newspaper has a small circulation approaching
50,000, said Luo, adding that the Science Daily will attempt to
increase its circulation by 10-fold over the three years. The
effort will focus on expanding content and covering major
scientific issues both at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
He said the restructuring will be carried out in tandem with
the Knowledge Innovation Project introduced by the CAS earlier
this year. The new daily will employ a staff of young reporters
and editors, and will assume full responsibility for profits and
losses.
</P>
<P>
The State Press and Publications Administration has approved
the restructuring project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
