<HEADLINE> Tourist Arrivals in Nepal Up in First 9 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Tourist arrivals by air in
Nepal in the first nine months of this year were 267,650, up 10.1
percent over the same period of last year, official figures show.
</P>
<P>
Figures provided Thursday by the Ministry of Tourism and Civil
Aviation show that during this period, tourist arrivals by air
from India were 108,231, up 10.6 percent over the same period of
last year.
</P>
<P>
Arrivals from other countries and regions grew by 9.7 percent
to 159,419.
</P>
<P>
Nepal has designated this year as Visit Nepal Year, in which it
aims to attract 500,000 tourists.
</P>
<P>
Tourism is one of the major foreign exchange earners of the
country, which used to have an average of 300,000 tourists
annually in the past years.
</P>
<P>
As the Austrian Airlines and the Transavia Airlines of the
Netherlands began last month regular flights to Kathmandu, more
European tourists are expected to be brought in. 
</P>
</TEXT>
