<HEADLINE> Ningxia Reaps Good Grain Harvest for 14 Straight Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, October 8 (Xinhua) -- The Ningxia Hui Autonomous
Region expects to harvest 2.96 billion kilograms of grain this
year, a 13.5 percent year-on-year increase over 1997 and an
all-time high for the region.
</P>
<P>
This will be the 14th consecutive good harvest for
Ningxia, a major grain producer in China.
</P>
<P>
The net grain increase for this year is estimated at 350
million kilograms, which equals the region's entire grain output
in 1949, when New China was founded.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, local farmers have reclaimed and made
use of 13,333 hectares of formerly wasteland and idle land.
</P>
<P>
The total grain-growing area of Ningxia is 822,000 hectares
this year, 40,000 hectares more than last year.
</P>
<P>
The application of agro-technology is playing a vital role in
raising grain output, according to regional authorities. 
</P>
