<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan diplomat Nihal
Rodrigo has been nominated the next secretary-general of the
seven-nation South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation
(SAARC), the SAARC Secretariat said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
He will take over the post in January 1999 when the incumbent
Secretary-General Naeem U. Hasan completes his three-year term.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan government communicated its nomination to SAARC
member countries during a meeting of SAARC foreign ministers held
on September 29 in New Delhi, India, the SAARC Secretariat said.
</P>
<P>
Nihal Rodrigo, additional secretary at the Sri Lankan Ministry
of Foreign Affairs, has been closely associated with SAARC process
since its inception in December 1985, it said.
</P>
<P>
He had served in Bonn, New Delhi, Canberra, Geneva and New York
representing Sri Lanka, the secretariat added.
</P>
<P>
The post of SAARC secretary-general is rotated in alphabetical
order among its seven member countries -- Bangladesh, Bhutan,
India, the Maldives, Nepal, Pakistan and Sri Lanka. 
