<HEADLINE> Gansu Power Industry Uses Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, October 8 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Gansu Province
was able to add 220,000 kw of generating capacity during the
January-August period this year thanks to the introduction 420
million US dollars in investments and government loans from
overseas.
</P>
<P>
The influx of funding represented a 70-fold rise on the figure
for 1993, with the French government leading the way in terms of
foreign investments in the power industry.
</P>
<P>
The influx of foreign funding has not only helped to ease power
shortages, but has also fueled local economic development.
</P>
<P>
Second phase construction at the Jingyuan Power Plant was
completed in 1997 with a 100 million US dollar investment from
the United States.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the Pingliang Power Plant is proceeding
smoothly, with the project benefitting greatly from Japanese loans
totalling 250 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The province has also attracted funds totalling 17.8 million US
dollars from France, Austria and Canada to refurbish the Liujiaxia
Hydropower Plant, the first power plant in the country with a
generating capacity of one million kilowatts. 
</P>
