<HEADLINE> East China Province Accelerates Highway Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, October 8 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang Province
plans to allocate 11 billion yuan for highway construction this
year, up 48 percent on last year's figure.
</P>
<P>
Plans have been made calling for the province to complete
highways stretching 680 km within the year, including expressway
mileage of some 172 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The province's total highway mileage will hit 37,212 km by the
end of the year, with that of expressway reaching 520 km.
</P>
<P>
Projects slated for the year include the provincial section of
the Shanghai-Hangzhou Expressway, the Ningbo-Taizhou-Wenzhou and
Hangzhou-Nanjing expressways, and the Jiaojiang Bridge in Taizhou.
</P>
<P>
The province allocated 5.96 billion yuan for highway
construction between January and August this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
