<HEADLINE> Beijing Newspaper Readership Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 8 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Newspaper and
Magazine Publishing Bureau reports that some seven million copies
of over 5,700 newspapers and magazines are distributed in Beijing
on a daily basis.
</P>
<P>
Major modes of distribution include the postal service and some
2,000 newspaper stands scattered throughout the city.
</P>
<P>
Experts point to two main factors contributing to the
popularity of newspapers and magazines: the city's cultural
tradition which dates back over 3,000 year, and the fact that
Beijing, the political and cultural center of China, is home to a
large number of highly educated people.
</P>
<P>
The city is the base for most national newspapers, with the
large number of local newspapers from other areas adding color to
the local newspaper market and increasing the local readership.
</P>
</TEXT>
