<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Measures Promote Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU October 8 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital of south
China's Guangdong Province, recently adopted a series of measures
to ensure fulfillment of this year's 13 percent economic growth
target.
</P>
<P>
The measures include expanding the city's domestic commodities
market, and the establishment of more distribution centers in
major Chinese cities to reduce costs involved in the city's
products to enter related markets at a lower costs.
</P>
<P>
Priority will also be placed on the construction of
infrastructure and various projects likely to promote rapid
economic growth, including telecommunications, water conservancy,
housing and high-tech projects.
</P>
<P>
The city government plans to help profitable enterprises repay
bank loans, and has already adopted 12 policies to boost foreign
trade.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou's gross domestic products for the January-August
period hit 108.5 billion yuan (13.1 billion US dollars), up 17
percent on the 1997 period. 
</P>
