<HEADLINE> Mexico Wish to Promote Ties With Honduras: President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Mexico is most interested in
strengthening commercial and financial links with Honduras,
Mexican President Ernesto Zedillo said Wednesday in welcoming
Honduran President Carlos Flores Facusse on a visit to Mexico.
</P>
<P>
The Mexican leader said that his government's efforts and the
current visit by Flores Facusse will help clear the way for the
signing of a regional free trade agreement over the next few
months.
</P>
