<HEADLINE> China's Largest Pilot Training Center Opens in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 8 (Xinhua) -- The China Eastern Airlines
Group and its subsidiary companies have opened the nation's
largest and also most advanced pilot training center in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Eastern Flight Training Center, established at a
cost of 100 million US dollars, is located in the Pudong New
Area's Waigaoqiao Bonded Zone. The complex has a floor space
of 20,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
The multifunctional complex consists of flight training
facilities, classrooms, offices and an entertainment venue. The
center features six types of simulators and offers
comprehensive inflight simulation and both theory and language
instruction.
</P>
<P>
The new center was established on the basis of the old China
Eastern Airlines training complex which trained over 4,000
pilots. 
</P>
