<HEADLINE> Peru's Fish Exports Expected to Fall Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Peru's fish exports this year may
drop by 58 percent from last year to 590 million U.S. dollars,
according to the National Fishing Society (NFS).
</P>
<P>
From January to September 1998, fish exports of the country
stood at 413 million dollars and are expected to generate 176
million for the rest of the year, the NFS said.
</P>
<P>
NFS General Manager Richard Diaz was quoted on Wednesday as
saying that in the first nine months of the year, fish catch
totaled only 2.21 million tons, 66.8 percent less than in the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
He added that although the El Nino phenomenon came to an end in
July, but the fishing sector's recovery cannot be so soon because
of the high salinity levels in the sea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
