<HEADLINE> Rainstorm Hits Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 7 (Xinhua) -- A rainstorm is wreaking havoc in
most parts of Italy and inflicting huge economic losses on the
country.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the Ministry of Environment say the unusually hot
weather and the excessive felling of trees are responsible for the
heavy rain.
</P>
<P>
For three consecutive days, the rain poured down in the
northern city of Udine, where water in some parts ran as deep as
one meter.
</P>
<P>
A 200-meter-long landslide blocked road traffic in the
outskirts of the central city of Terni. On Wednesday, the
international airport in Rome was closed for half an hour due to
the heavy rain.
</P>
<P>
In the southern cities of Bari, Salerno and Palermo, rivers
overflowed their banks and the floods washed away roads and many
other facilities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
