<HEADLINE> Brazil's GDP Up 1.44 Percent in Second Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's gross domestic
product (GDP) grew by 1.44 percent in the second quarter over
previous quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
According to the Brazilian Geography and Statistics Institute
(BGSI),the GDP increase represented a 1.53 percent rise compared
to the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Among the three sectors that make up GDP, the agricultural
sector had a 4.31 percent increase in the period, followed by
the industrial sector with a 1.65 percent increase and the
services sector which recorded a 1.01 percent increase, BGSI said.
</P>
<P>
The country's GDP went up 1.22 percent on a year-on-year basis
during the first half of this year. 
</P>
