<HEADLINE> Top Seeds Crashed out of Swiss Indoors Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, October 7 (Xinhua) -- Top seeds Pete Sampras of the
United States and Patrick Rafter of Australia both crashed out in
the first round of the Swiss Indoors tennis tournament in Basel
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, Wimbledon Open champion, was edged out by South
Afrtican Wayne Ferreira 4-6, 7-6 (7-4), 6-3 only hours after
Rafter was eliminated in straight sets by Czech Daniel Vacek.
</P>
<P>
"I'm very disappointed," said Sampras, who received a wildcard
in Basel in an effort to finish as world No. 1 in the rankings
this year. "It can't get much worse than this."
</P>
<P>
In the day other upset, two-time U.S. Open champion Rafter
lost 7-6 (9-7), 7-5 to the 44th-ranked Vacek.
</P>
<P>
Sampras' and Rafter's elimination marks the exit of the
tournament's biggest draws and all three Grand Slam champions
present this year. Petr Korda, the Australian Open champion, lost
in the first round on Tuesday to Germany's Nicolas Kiefer, 6-2,
6-4. 
