<HEADLINE> U.S. to Provide 260 Aircraft for Kosovo Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 7 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. has told the North
Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) it could provide about 260
aircraft for a military operation in Kosovo should one be ordered,
a Pentagon official said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The warplanes offered include two B-2 stealth bombers, a dozen
F-117 stealth fighters, six B-52 bombers, the Navy's 70 aircraft
on board the aircraft carrier USS Eisenhower and dozens of Air
Force F-15s and F-16s based in Europe, said the official who spoke
on condition of anonymity.
</P>
<P>
Should the B-2 be ordered into combat, it would be the first
such use of the bat-winged bomber.
</P>
<P>
No movement orders have been issued for any of the aircraft at
this time, the official was quoted by an Associated Press (AP)
report as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
