<HEADLINE> Aziz: It Is Premature for Iraq to Resume Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 7 (Xinhua) -- It was premature for Iraq
to resume cooperation with the U.N. arms inspectors, Iraq's Deputy
Prime Minister Tareq Aziz said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after meeting with Secretary-General Kofi
Annan, Aziz said, "It is premature to say anything about that. We
have to weigh the situation and I have asked for further
clarifications."
</P>
<P>
Aziz, who has been here for over a week, will leave for Baghdad
Wednesday afternoon. He has had three rounds of talks with the
U.N. chief, which aimed to find a solution to the current standoff
between Iraq and the U.N. over the arms inspection. 
</P>
